{
    "title": "Pronouns",
    "description": "Refer to yourself and groups of people, and learn common Swahili questions/statements.",
    "image": "introducing-yourself.jpg",
    "unit": "basic-conversation",
    "lesson": [
        {
            "instruction": "Remember how to say <code>me</code> and <code>you</code>?",
            "english": "me and you",
            "swahili": "mimi~I na~and wewe~you",
            "uuid": "23b5e47d-76b2-4d49-9860-3853f2411c76"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "Notice that Swahili pronouns don't change based on gender.",
            "english": "him/her",
            "swahili": "yeye",
            "uuid": "e52ad9b6-15cb-441d-bc8d-4f44905478f8"
        },
        {
            "english": "He is American.",
            "swahili": "__=Yeye ni Mmarekani__.",
            "uuid": "01bfe3e4-68ec-404d-848c-713c1a3e01f7",
            "instruction": ""
        },
        {
            "instruction": "Let's use pronouns that requires us to talk about two or more people.",
            "english": "we",
            "swahili": "sisi",
            "uuid": "18d9f10a-c1da-4fe1-99d9-ccfdc7e26438"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "When referring to a plural number of Americans, Tanzanians, or Africans, the <code>M</code> prefix becomes <code>Wa</code>. Unlike English, many Swahili nouns and adjectives change based on whether they are used in a singular or plural context.",
            "english": "Americans, Africans, Tanzanians",
            "swahili": "Wamarekani, Waafrika, Watanzania",
            "uuid": "7e8eb747-5555-4830-a5d6-5543373b30e2"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "Use the plural form of \"African\" here.",
            "english": "We are African.",
            "swahili": "__=Sisi ni Waafrika__.",
            "uuid": "35e170bd-0e27-4da3-8b1e-81dc0bbf49a4"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "This is the pronoun you would use to directly address more than one person. Sometimes this pronoun will be pronounced and spelled as <code>ninyi</code>, but we will use the more common <code>nyinyi</code>.",
            "english": "you all <span class=\"muted\">(plural)</span>",
            "swahili": "nyinyi",
            "uuid": "77a4678f-4128-4e8d-ae94-425b9e8bdd51"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "How would you ask this question? Remember to use the plural form of \"Tanzanian\".",
            "english": "Are you all Tanzanian?",
            "swahili": "__=Nyinyi ni Watanzania__?",
            "uuid": "35e170bd-0e27-4da3-8b1e-81dc0bbf49a4"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "When greeting more than one person, use the greeting <code>hamjambo</code> instead of <code>hujambo</code>.",
            "english": "Hello, how are you all?",
            "swahili": "Hamjambo, habari gani?",
            "uuid": "e82ee002-5a74-4e64-867f-b905e4c2667a"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "When responding to <code>hamjambo</code>, use <code>hatujambo</code> instead of <code>sijambo</code>.",
            "english": "Hello, we are good.",
            "swahili": "Hatujambo, sisi~we ni nzuri~good .",
            "uuid": "663f8c1e-2cdf-4a92-9f10-b9d52955da2a"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "Use <code>wao</code> to indirectly refer to more than one person.",
            "english": "they/them",
            "swahili": "wao",
            "uuid": "f46fcf93-4b35-4c95-932d-dd0d49174ff6"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "Remember the word for \"okay\" is the same as the word for \"good\", <code>nzuri</code>. However, since this is used in a plural context, <code>nzuri</code> changes to <code>wazuri</code>.",
            "english": "Are they okay?",
            "swahili": "__=Wao ni wazuri?__",
            "uuid": "1af79465-fd60-4f80-81c4-ca628e75c878"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "Fill in the pronouns and adjective. Notice the word for \"bad\" is <code>mbaya</code>.",
            "english": "He is bad, but they all are good.",
            "swahili": "__=Yeye__ ni~is mbaya~bad , lakini~but __=wao__ ni~are __=wazuri__.",
            "uuid": "9a9f017b-fa44-4b04-9e4d-d4dd48b724b9"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "What do you think is the plural form of <code>mbaya</code> (bad)?",
            "english": "We are bad.",
            "swahili": "__=Sisi ni wabaya__.",
            "uuid": "36ea05c4-3bbf-46e9-9c24-b3769580a9a8"
        }
    ]
}
